    • Field Detail

      • activity

        protected Activity activity
        Activity to which this is linked. Is null iff the ActivityEvent is not linked to an Activity

      • inProgress

        private boolean inProgress
        True if the activityEvent method action is called for the first time, false the second time (no third time) The point is to have the method action called twice with different behaviours, whether it is the start or the end the activityEvent

      • delay

        protected int delay
        minimal number of minutes after which another ActivityEvent can be executed. Is used with the .schedule(int delay)

      • lateness

        private int lateness
        Model the gap, in minutes, between the activity programmed in a schedule and this.

    • Constructor Detail

      • ActivityEvent

        public ActivityEvent()
        The activity is set to null, the lateness to 0 and the delay to -1 (suggesting that this cannot happen as long as generateDelay() is not called) , inProgress to false. See ActivityEvent

        Specified by:

      • startActions

        public abstract void startActions()
        actions needed to be performed at the beginning of the corresponding activity, if the conditions are respected, see conditions(). For actions that are done during the activity, and can be considered to be done only at the end of the activity, see endActions().

      • conditions

        public abstract boolean conditions()
        if this method returns true, the actions linked to that activity will be done, see startActions() and endActions()
        Returns:
        true if the conditions necessary to do the activity are respected.

      • endActions

        public abstract void endActions()
        actions supposed to happen during the event, the actions will all occur at the end of the activityEvent. Warning : these actions can only be done if the conditions for the activity are respected, see conditions().

      • clone

        public abstract ActivityEvent clone()
        Each ActivityEvent child class has its own impletementation of that method.

      • isInProgress

        public boolean isInProgress()
        Returns:
